set nocompatible "  This option has the effect of making Vim either more Vi-compatible, or make Vim behave in a more useful way.
set tabstop=2 " Changes number of spaces tab inserts to 2
set expandtab " Changes all new tab characters to spaces
set shiftwidth=2 " Changes the number of space characters inserted for indentation
set number " Displays line numbers 
set ls=2 " This makes Vim show a status line even when only one window is shown.
set ruler " Shows the "ruler" for the cursor, ie its current position with line+column and the percentage within the buffer.
set backspace=indent,eol,start " Makes backspace work like in most other programs
set bg=dark " Improves syntax highlighting for a black background
set backup " Turns on backing up  
set backupdir=~/.backup " Assigns ~/.backup to be the back up directory
set directory=~/.vimswap " Saves swap files to ~/.vimswap
